attachments.title: Watch the Clavilux, an ethereal light organ from 100 years ago - Create Digital Music
attachments.text: Long before trippy visualizers and computer animation, before liquid light shows or laser parties, Thomas Wilfred was building organs for visuals. He called the art they produced Lumia, and the instrument Clavilux – a keyboard for light. That first instrument was built all the way back in 1919. But unlike a lot of the spectacles … Continue →
